metadata.name: In Flow #131
metadata.description:
In Flow is the first in a series of four projects exploring flow fields, produced with 100% code in p5.js.  This one has a consistent gap between flow lines and a low noise resolution, producing a wispy effect that often looks like thread or felt.  Sometimes the background is a bit garish, which can be fun.  There's a good chance some texture will be added in the end, either mixing the colors and softening, or adding a fine paper texture.  It finishes off with a grain shader by Dave Pegurek found here: https://editor.p5js.org/davepagurek/sketches/m6p09ERHx

After opening, hit 2 - 5 for higher pixel densities, and 's' to save a png. Resizing the canvas reverts to pixel density 1.

Come visit my YouTube channel for generative art how-to videos: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCJjYUJudUW67Tg79jtF_rpQ

metadata.name: Late Night Sketches #133
metadata.description:
This project is part of an experiment combining hand-drawn "squiggles" and turning them into something unexpected. 

The assets used in this project were hand-drawn with markers, pens, brushes, and ink. I will sit down for several hours and draw a page of elements in one of my sketchbooks. I then scan the drawings and separate them into transparent png files in Photoshop. Then the p5.js sketch takes those images and places them according to a grid. 

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: print size @ 3000px x 3000px

metadata.name: Fragment Assembler #64
metadata.description:
Fragment Assembler is a chaos engine that creates complex abstract patterns and textures. As the artwork is drawn, it constantly recomposes itself during assembly with a series of displacement techniques, creating new forms and visual elements, while others get broken into pieces and textures. The work is orientation agnostic, and will display the output in portrait orientation on tall displays.

Intended to display on high resolution mode. The artwork renders with lower resolution by default to maintain compatibility with lower end devices. 

Press '2' to double the internal resolution (recommended).
Press 'h' to enable full internal resolution (requires a modern desktop computer).
Press space bar to reload the work.
Press 's' to save the output as PNG.
To render a 6k PNG, first press 'h', then save with 'p' (requires a modern desktop computer).


Made with p5.js & WebGL.
Best displayed with a modern desktop system & Chrome browser.

metadata.name: I wish for the metaverse ... #50
metadata.description:
I WISH FOR THE METAVERSE TO RINSE OFF OF ME is a collection about both the power and the infirmity of affirmations. Shamanic, mantra-like, willful, affirmations seek to map a desired direction. That is, until time and mind get in the way.  Within brief, passing moments, our minds are able to manifest conflicting wishes—and do so via declarative, convincing statements. 
 
This work plays inside the chasm that divides intention and action. If we don’t know what we want, how can we act? Without the commitment of mind along the vast axis of time, our affirmations risk becoming sloganistic, simplistic, unrealistic—wavering proclamations that announce our vulnerability. 
 
Key words in these algorithmic affirmations shift over time to reflect the way our minds fluctuate. By shuffling words, this collection also explores our fluid relation to language. How to construct meaningful lives, when signification changes, moment to moment, within our minds? 
 
I WISH FOR THE METAVERSE TO RINSE OFF OF ME is a performance of fragility, which is where our humanity—and our beauty—abounds.

-return will resume the animation

metadata.name: Pensado a mano #132
metadata.description:
WARNING: Read instructions so you don’t get a broken token!!
----


Q: Why haven’t you tried fx(params)?
A: Pff.. Sliders?


“Pensado a mano” explores the intersection of Generative Art and Hand Drawing. The collector, by drawing a predefined number of shapes on canvas, creates a unique hand-crafted seed that generates the final artwork. That is the only customisable param, thought by hand, which interacts with various random attributes to produce a unique composition.

“…the time we spend doing and making things, the process…”

And yet the process continues. On the background, the code generates a plottable svg.
An artificially extended process, from hand to screen, from screen to paper, that creates a new kind of mixed media.

Signed plots will soon be claimable via Artfora (tbd price + shipping)


INSTRUCTIONS

1 - Draw the requested shapes and wait to see the result. You can change the Seed Nr. slider if you don't like the selected mode.
2 - Press “C” to copy drawing to Clipboard
3 - Copy the clipboard contents to the text-input on the fx(params) sidebar

***Important. If you buy several tickets, make sure you don't mint the same Seed Nr. twice (slider)

press “S” to save the PNG, press “P” to plot the SVG


DISCLAIMER

This is a high-supply token minted during a bear market. Have Fun.

metadata.name: Digital Gardens #17
metadata.description:
Digital Gardens are places of magic and wonder, where you can connect with your inner nature and take a deep breath. Digital Gardens are a refuge from the world outside. A sanctuary for the mind, body, and soul. But they are also a place of play and exploration. It is a space where you can let your imagination run wild, creating and discovering new things.
Digital Gardens brings to life the minimalistic essence of Detegus’ art and the abstract and rational art of Alfredo Boaron.
The gardens are generated from a recursive function dividing the space at each iteration with a proportion that follows the Fibonacci succession and randomly stops after some iterations. At each recursion the canvas is divided into two pieces following the proportion of two consecutive Fibonacci numbers [1 to 144].
The minimalistic visual effect is then personalized by the palettes of 15 artists who embraced the invitation to give their personal contribution to the collection. The palette name and the author name is displayed in the features along with the Fibonacci numbers ratio, the colors number vs the total palette color number, the background color, the total number of rectangles and the depth level of recursion achieved by the algorithm.
Immerse yourself in this generative project, inspired by geometrism and abstract expressionism. 
Lose yourself in the beauty of a digital garden.
